# The Dockerfile does `COPY . .`, so this file is the control that keeps secrets and
# junk out of the image. Image layers are readable by anyone who can pull the image.

# Secrets. Non-negotiable.
.env
.env.*

# VCS and agent/editor state
.git
.gitignore
.claude
CLAUDE.md
.attic/

# Python build and environment artifacts
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.venv/
venv/
*.egg-info/

# Not needed at runtime -- except two files that ARE, so both negations are load-bearing.
#
#   the CSV:  without it the image builds clean and the app dies at import, because the
#             only thing it has to read is the one file we excluded.
#   the dict: a Tier-1 eval asserts DATA_DICTIONARY.md quotes skills.UNIT_NOTE verbatim, so
#             the doc cannot drift from the caveat users see. Exclude it and that eval fails
#             *only inside the image* -- green on the laptop, red in the artifact we ship,
#             which is the one place a reviewer runs it (see below). Caught by running it.
#
# The brief's PDF stays out: it is Owkin's confidential material (docs/*.pdf, .gitignore).
docs/
!docs/owkin_take_home_data.csv
!docs/DATA_DICTIONARY.md
README.md

# Generated audit log: working scaffolding (see .gitignore), and it reached 555 KB during
# development. It must not bloat or leak into the image. The data CSV is runtime-required
# and is NOT excluded -- and neither is evals.py: the README's section (b) is built on that
# suite, so a reviewer who only runs Docker must still be able to run it:
#   docker compose run --rm web python evals.py
query_audit.jsonl
*.jsonl

# OS noise
.DS_Store
